claim.claim-text:
1. A method for delivering a fluid to an animal, the method comprising the steps of:
a. providing a catheter;
b. inserting the catheter into the animal, so that a fluid can be injected or withdrawn from the animal;
c. providing first, second, third and fourth tubes;
d. providing a first syringe with a first outlet, wherein the first outlet includes a first syringe opening and a second syringe opening, and a second syringe with a second outlet, wherein the second outlet includes a third syringe opening and a fourth syringe opening;
e. providing first and second fluid reservoirs;
f. providing a first valve having a first fluid control position adapted to receive the first tube therethrough and a second fluid control position adapted to receive the second tube therethrough, wherein when the first fluid control position is closed, the second fluid control position is open, and vice versa;
g. providing a second valve having a third fluid control position adapted to receive the third tube therethrough and a fourth fluid control position adapted to receive the fourth tube therethrough, wherein when the third fluid control position is closed, the fourth fluid control position is open, and vice versa;
h. operatively connecting one end of the first tube to the first fluid reservoir and another end of the first tube to the first syringe opening;
i. operatively connecting one end of the second tube to the second syringe opening and operatively connecting another end of the second tube to both one end of the fourth tube and to a system output, wherein the second tube operatively connects the first syringe to a system output;
j. operatively connecting one end of the third tube to the second fluid reservoir and another end of the third tube to the third syringe opening;
k. operatively connecting one end of the fourth tube to the fourth syringe opening and operatively connecting another end of the fourth tube to both one end of the second tube and to the system output, wherein the fourth tube operatively connects the second syringe to the system output;
l. operatively coupling one end of the catheter to the system output;
m. flushing the system output and the catheter by injecting a first fluid comprising a flushing fluid in the first syringe by closing the fourth fluid control position of the second valve, opening the second fluid control position of the first valve, and pushing the first syringe so that the first fluid in the first syringe will flow through the second tube, into the system output, through the catheter, whereby the first position of the first valve prevents the first fluid in the first syringe from flowing into the first reservoir; and
n. injecting a second fluid comprising a drug in the second syringe into the animal by closing the second fluid control position of the first valve, opening the fourth fluid control position of the second valve, and pushing the second syringe so that the second fluid in the second syringe will flow through the fourth tube, into the system output, through the catheter and into the animal, whereby the third position of the second valve prevents the second fluid in the second syringe from flowing into the second reservoir.

4. The method of claim 3, further comprising the steps of:
q. opening the first position of the first valve, opening the fourth position of the second valve and opening the fifth position of the third valve;
r. causing the first and second syringe pumps to pull the first and second syringes, respectively, so that a body fluid of the animal appears in the catheter outlet and the first syringe fills with the first fluid;
s. opening the second position of the first valve and opening the fifth position of the third valve; and
t. causing the first syringe pump to push the first syringe, so that the first fluid flushes the system outlet and the catheter.

8. The method of claim 1, wherein steps (h)-(k) further comprise:
h. operatively connecting one end of the first tube to the first fluid reservoir and another end of the first tube to the first syringe first opening via a first T-connector;
i. operatively connecting one end of the second tube to the second syringe opening via the first T-connector and operatively connecting another end of the second tube to a first Y-connector, wherein the first Y-connector operably connects the end of the second tube to both one end of the fourth tube and one end of the system output, wherein the Y-connector connects the first syringe to the system output;
j. operatively connecting one end of the third tube to the second fluid reservoir and another end of the third tube to the third syringe opening via a second T-connector;
k. operatively connecting one end of the fourth tube to the fourth syringe opening via the second T-connector and operatively connecting another end of the fourth tube to the first Y-connector, wherein the first Y-connector operably connect the end of the fourth tube to both one end of the second tube and one end of the system output, wherein the Y-connector connects the second syringe to the system output.

13. A method for delivering a fluid to an animal, the method comprising the steps of:
a. providing a catheter;
b. inserting the catheter into the animal, so that a fluid can be injected or withdrawn from the animal;
c. providing a first syringe with a first outlet, wherein the outlet includes a first syringe opening and a second syringe opening, and a second syringe with a second outlet, wherein the second outlet includes a third syringe opening and a fourth syringe opening;
d. providing first and second fluid reservoirs;
e. interruptibly connecting the fluid flow from the first fluid reservoir to the first syringe opening;
f. interruptibly connecting the fluid flow from the second syringe opening to the fourth syringe opening and to a system output;
g. interruptibly connecting the fluid flow from the second fluid reservoir to the third syringe opening;
h. interruptibly connecting the fluid flow from the fourth syringe opening to the second syringe opening and to the system output;
i. interruptibly coupling one end of the catheter to the system output; and
j. flushing the system output and catheter by injecting a first fluid comprising a flushing fluid in the first syringe by interrupting the connection of fluid flow between the first fluid reservoir and the first syringe opening, interrupting the connection of fluid flow between the fourth syringe opening and the system output, and pushing the first syringe so that the first fluid in the first syringe will flow through the catheter; and
k. injecting a second fluid comprising a drug in the second syringe into the animal by interrupting the connection of fluid flow between the second fluid reservoir and the third syringe opening, interrupting the connection of fluid flow between the second syringe opening and the system output, and pushing the second syringe so that the second fluid in the second syringe will flow through the catheter and into the animal, whereby the interrupted connection prevents the second fluid in the second syringe from flowing into the second reservoir.

18. The method of claim 17, further comprising the steps of:
n. operating the second valve to interrupt the connection of fluid flow between the second syringe opening and the system output, operating the third valve to interrupt the connection of fluid flow between the third syringe opening and the second reservoir, operating the fourth valve to prevent interruption of the connection between the fourth syringe opening and the system output, and operating the fifth valve to prevent the interruption of the connection between the catheter and the system output;
o. causing the second syringe pump to pull the second syringe, so that a body fluid of the animal flows into the second syringe from the catheter;
p. causing the first syringe pump to pull the first syringe, so that the first syringe fills with saline from the first fluid reservoir;
q. operating the first valve to interrupt the connection between the first syringe opening and the first reservoir, operating the second valve to prevent interruption of the connection between the second syringe opening and the system output, operating the fourth valve to interrupt the connection between the fourth syringe opening and the system output, and operating the fifth valve to prevent the interruption of the connection between the catheter and the system output; and
r. causing the first syringe pump to push the first syringe, so that the saline flushes the system outlet and the catheter.
